ole of Hindu civilization. The present edition forms a part of J. A. B. van Buitenen's widely acclaimed translation of this great work. Here English and Sanskrit are printed on facing pages, enabling those with some knowledge of Sanskrit to appreciate van Buitenen's accurate rendering of the intimate, familial tone and directness of the original poem.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Jun 2022) 7aRELIGION / General.2bisacsh  ashrimad bhagavad gita, hinduism, hindu, religious, religion, scripture, mahabharata, bhishma parva, pandava, prince arjuna, krishna, vishnu, incarnation, dharma yuddha, righteous war, moral dilemma, selfless action, ethics, philosophy, sanskrit, song of the lord, battle, duty, death, kingdom, power, warrior, theology, theological, metaphysics, culture, civilization, poem, translation, translated work, epic literature, devotional.1 aO’More, Haven, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 avan Buitenen, J. A. B.40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780226219028423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780226219028/original  aGBV-deGruyter-alles